# Bridge23 Development Guidelines

## Project Overview

This project, named Bridge23, is a superior team and community management platform built using Next.js and TypeScript. It provides automated planning and task execution capabilities for teams and communities.

## Key URLs

- Website: <https://bridge23.app/>
- Beta App: <https://beta.bridge23.app/>

## Project Structure

- **app/**: Next.js app directory for routing and pages
- **components/**: Reusable UI components
- **public/**: Static assets and images
- **types/**: TypeScript type definitions
- **styles/**: Global styles and CSS

## Development Guidelines

- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow the coding standards defined in ESLint configuration
- Ensure all components are responsive and accessible
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow the established design system and color palette

## Responsive Design Rules

- Use mobile-first approach for all components
- Follow these breakpoints:
  - Mobile: < 768px (default)
  - Tablet: md:768px
  - Desktop: lg:1024px
  - Large Desktop: xl:1280px
- Implement responsive typography:
  - Base size for mobile
  - md: for tablet
  - lg: for desktop
- Use flexbox/grid for responsive layouts
- Test all components across devices
- Ensure touch-friendly UI for mobile

## Component Guidelines

- Create reusable components in the components/ directory
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces
- Implement responsive design using Tailwind CSS classes:
  - Padding: p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8
  - Margin: m-4 md:m-6 lg:m-8
  - Font size: text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg
  - Width: w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3
- Follow accessibility best practices
- Add proper documentation and props typing

## Layout Rules

- Use container classes for consistent width
- Implement proper spacing:
  - Section padding: py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-24
  - Content margin: mb-8 md:mb-12 lg:mb-16
- Handle navigation responsively:
  - Mobile menu for small screens
  - Desktop menu for larger screens
- Ensure proper image sizing and optimization

## Important Scripts

- `npm run dev`: Starts the development server
- `npm run build`: Builds the application for production
- `npm run start`: Runs the production server

## Coding Standards

- Use TypeScript for all new components and functions
- Follow React best practices and hooks guidelines
- Maintain consistent component structure
- Write clear, self-documenting code
- Handle errors gracefully and provide user feedback

